      "date": "2011-04-23 04:06:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis is almost the same version as 22040.\nAlex, You were right that we send garbage in the new owner field, but I did some tests and it seems whoever calls this code is in fact doing happen to leave something of uniq id for the process being run on both x86_64 and i686 so the behavior between before and after the patch is unchanged,\nas such I propose not to waste any connection bits still, esp. since next to nobody uses bsd locks anyway.\n\nJohann: Aside from inspecting, I think we need this for 1.8.6 too (and back out patch from 22660) so please consider and if so, let me know and I can produce 1.8 version too.",
